verses.text_plain: Then all Israel gathered themselves to David unto Hebron, saying, Behold, we are thy bone and thy flesh.
verses.verse_html: 1Then all Israel gathered themselves to David unto Hebron, saying, Behold, we are thy bone and thy flesh.

verses.text_plain: And moreover in time past, even when Saul was king, thou wast he that leddest out and broughtest in Israel: and the Lord thy God said unto thee, Thou shalt feed my people Israel, and thou shalt be ruler over my people Israel.
verses.verse_html:
2And moreover in time past, even when Saul was king, thou wast he that leddest out and broughtest in Israel: and the Lord thy God said unto thee, Thou shalt feed my people Israel, and thou shalt be ruler over my people Israel. ▼
▼ in time…: Heb. both yesterday and the third day
 , ▼
▼ feed: or, rule

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in time…: Heb. both yesterday and the third day
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in time…: Heb. both yesterday and the third day

verses.text_plain: Therefore came all the elders of Israel to the king to Hebron; and David made a covenant with them in Hebron before the Lord; and they anointed David king over Israel, according to the word of the Lord by Samuel.
verses.verse_html:
3Therefore came all the elders of Israel to the king to Hebron; and David made a covenant with them in Hebron before the Lord; and they anointed David king over Israel, according to the word of the Lord by Samuel. ▼
▼ by: Heb. by the hand of

footnotes.body_text: ▼ by: Heb. by the hand of
footnotes.body_html: ▼ by: Heb. by the hand of

verses.text_plain: And David and all Israel went to Jerusalem, which is Jebus; where the Jebusites were, the inhabitants of the land.
verses.verse_html: 4And David and all Israel went to Jerusalem, which is Jebus; where the Jebusites were, the inhabitants of the land.

verses.text_plain: And the inhabitants of Jebus said to David, Thou shalt not come hither. Nevertheless David took the castle of Zion, which is the city of David.
verses.verse_html: 5And the inhabitants of Jebus said to David, Thou shalt not come hither. Nevertheless David took the castle of Zion, which is the city of David.

verses.text_plain: And David said, Whosoever smiteth the Jebusites first shall be chief and captain. So Joab the son of Zeruiah went first up, and was chief.
verses.verse_html:
6And David said, Whosoever smiteth the Jebusites first shall be chief and captain. So Joab the son of Zeruiah went first up, and was chief. ▼
▼ chief: Heb. head

verses.text_plain: And David dwelt in the castle; therefore they called it the city of David.
verses.verse_html:
7And David dwelt in the castle; therefore they called it the city of David. ▼
▼ it: that is, Zion

footnotes.body_html: ▼ it: that is, Zion

verses.text_plain: And he built the city round about, even from Millo round about: and Joab repaired the rest of the city.
verses.verse_html:
8And he built the city round about, even from Millo round about: and Joab repaired the rest of the city. ▼
▼ repaired: Heb. revived

verses.text_plain: So David waxed greater and greater: for the Lord of hosts was with him.
verses.verse_html:
9So David waxed greater and greater: for the Lord of hosts was with him. ▼
▼ waxed…: Heb. went in going and increasing

footnotes.body_text: ▼ waxed…: Heb. went in going and increasing
footnotes.body_html: ▼ waxed…: Heb. went in going and increasing

verses.text_plain: These also are the chief of the mighty men whom David had, who strengthened themselves with him in his kingdom, and with all Israel, to make him king, according to the word of the Lord concerning Israel.
verses.verse_html:
10These also are the chief of the mighty men whom David had, who strengthened themselves with him in his kingdom, and with all Israel, to make him king, according to the word of the Lord concerning Israel. ▼
▼ strengthened…: or, held strongly with him

tokens.text: themselves with him in his kingdom

footnotes.body_text: ▼ strengthened…: or, held strongly with him
footnotes.body_html: ▼ strengthened…: or, held strongly with him

verses.text_plain: And this is the number of the mighty men whom David had; Jashobeam, an Hachmonite, the chief of the captains: he lifted up his spear against three hundred slain by him at one time.
verses.verse_html:
11And this is the number of the mighty men whom David had; Jashobeam, an Hachmonite, the chief of the captains: he lifted up his spear against three hundred slain by him at one time. ▼
▼ an Hachmonite: or, son of Hachmoni

footnotes.body_text: ▼ an Hachmonite: or, son of Hachmoni
footnotes.body_html: ▼ an Hachmonite: or, son of Hachmoni

verses.text_plain: And after him was Eleazar the son of Dodo, the Ahohite, who was one of the three mighties.
verses.verse_html: 12And after him was Eleazar the son of Dodo, the Ahohite, who was one of the three mighties.

verses.text_plain: He was with David at Pas–dammim, and there the Philistines were gathered together to battle, where was a parcel of ground full of barley; and the people fled from before the Philistines.
verses.verse_html:
13He was with David at Pas–dammim, and there the Philistines were gathered together to battle, where was a parcel of ground full of barley; and the people fled from before the Philistines. ▼
▼ Pas–dammim: also called, Ephes–dammim

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Pas–dammim: also called, Ephes–dammim

verses.text_plain: And they set themselves in the midst of that parcel, and delivered it, and slew the Philistines; and the Lord saved them by a great deliverance.
verses.verse_html:
14And they set themselves in the midst of that parcel, and delivered it, and slew the Philistines; and the Lord saved them by a great deliverance. ▼
▼ set…: or, stood
 , ▼
▼ deliverance: or, salvation

verses.text_plain: Now three of the thirty captains went down to the rock to David, into the cave of Adullam; and the host of the Philistines encamped in the valley of Rephaim.
verses.verse_html:
15Now three of the thirty captains went down to the rock to David, into the cave of Adullam; and the host of the Philistines encamped in the valley of Rephaim. ▼
▼ three…: or, three captains over the thirty

footnotes.body_text: ▼ three…: or, three captains over the thirty
footnotes.body_html: ▼ three…: or, three captains over the thirty

verses.text_plain: And David was then in the hold, and the Philistines’ garrison was then at Beth–lehem.
verses.verse_html: 16And David was then in the hold, and the Philistines’ garrison was then at Beth–lehem.

verses.text_plain: And David longed, and said, Oh that one would give me drink of the water of the well of Beth–lehem, that is at the gate!
verses.verse_html: 17And David longed, and said, Oh that one would give me drink of the water of the well of Beth–lehem, that is at the gate!

tokens.text: Oh that one would give me drink

verses.text_plain: And the three brake through the host of the Philistines, and drew water out of the well of Beth–lehem, that was by the gate, and took it, and brought it to David: but David would not drink of it, but poured it out to the Lord,
verses.verse_html: 18And the three brake through the host of the Philistines, and drew water out of the well of Beth–lehem, that was by the gate, and took it, and brought it to David: but David would not drink of it, but poured it out to the Lord,

verses.text_plain: And said, My God forbid it me, that I should do this thing: shall I drink the blood of these men that have put their lives in jeopardy? for with the jeopardy of their lives they brought it. Therefore he would not drink it. These things did these three mightiest.
verses.verse_html:
19And said, My God forbid it me, that I should do this thing: shall I drink the blood of these men that have put their lives in jeopardy? for with the jeopardy of their lives they brought it. Therefore he would not drink it. These things did these three mightiest. ▼
▼ that have…: Heb. with their lives?

tokens.text: it me, that I should do
that have put their lives in jeopardy

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that have…: Heb. with their lives?
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that have…: Heb. with their lives?

verses.text_plain: And Abishai the brother of Joab, he was chief of the three: for lifting up his spear against three hundred, he slew them, and had a name among the three.
verses.verse_html: 20And Abishai the brother of Joab, he was chief of the three: for lifting up his spear against three hundred, he slew them, and had a name among the three.

verses.text_plain: Of the three, he was more honourable than the two; for he was their captain: howbeit he attained not to the first three.
verses.verse_html: 21Of the three, he was more honourable than the two; for he was their captain: howbeit he attained not to the first three.

verses.text_plain: Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man of Kabzeel, who had done many acts; he slew two lionlike men of Moab: also he went down and slew a lion in a pit in a snowy day.
verses.verse_html:
22Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man of Kabzeel, who had done many acts; he slew two lionlike men of Moab: also he went down and slew a lion in a pit in a snowy day. ▼
▼ who had…: Heb. great of deeds

footnotes.body_text: ▼ who had…: Heb. great of deeds
footnotes.body_html: ▼ who had…: Heb. great of deeds

verses.text_plain: And he slew an Egyptian, a man of great stature, five cubits high; and in the Egyptian’s hand was a spear like a weaver’s beam; and he went down to him with a staff, and plucked the spear out of the Egyptian’s hand, and slew him with his own spear.
verses.verse_html:
23And he slew an Egyptian, a man of great stature, five cubits high; and in the Egyptian’s hand was a spear like a weaver’s beam; and he went down to him with a staff, and plucked the spear out of the Egyptian’s hand, and slew him with his own spear. ▼
▼ great…: Heb. measure

verses.text_plain: These things did Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and had the name among the three mighties.
verses.verse_html: 24These things did Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and had the name among the three mighties.

verses.text_plain: Behold, he was honourable among the thirty, but attained not to the first three: and David set him over his guard.
verses.verse_html: 25Behold, he was honourable among the thirty, but attained not to the first three: and David set him over his guard.

verses.text_plain: Also the valiant men of the armies were, Asahel the brother of Joab, Elhanan the son of Dodo of Beth–lehem,
verses.verse_html: 26Also the valiant men of the armies were, Asahel the brother of Joab, Elhanan the son of Dodo of Beth–lehem,

verses.text_plain: Shammoth the Harorite, Helez the Pelonite,
verses.verse_html:
27Shammoth the Harorite, Helez the Pelonite, ▼
